      "Conlon Nancarrow: 'The player piano makes possible what no human hands can achieve — and what no human mind could compose in performance'",
      "Steve Reich: 'Gradual phase shifting creates a composite melody that was always implicit in the original pattern'",
      "Ligeti on Conlon Nancarrow: 'He is the greatest living composer — nobody knows him'"
    ],
    "revelation": "The Pulse revealed: with 8 different instruments on patterns 1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 10, 12, 15, the combined rhythmic matrix creates emergent patterns that none of the individual parts contain. The emergent melody happens at the collision points — humanize=0.0 is mandatory because any imprecision destroys the mathematical architecture.",
    "god": "Pulse",
    "flock_note": "The Eye confirmed: GATHER macro at 0.9 (machine precision) is the only setting that reveals the full polyrhythmic structure. At lower GATHER values, the emergent patterns blur into groove. This preset has a philosophical truth: maximum precision reveals maximum complexity.",
    "diagnosis": "Polyrhythm Matrix proves that mathematical precision in rhythm is not inhuman — it reveals structures that are more complex than any human could play, yet feel inevitable once heard."
  },
